For public ip
sudo nano /etc/openvpn/easy-rsa/pki/Default.txt

for server config:
sudo nano /etc/openvpn/server.conf

and:

sudo nano /etc/pivpn/openvpn/setupVars.conf

for clients certificates go to:
/etc/openvpn/ccd

if you change the hostname of your raspberry pivpn might not work properly
therefore you have to reinstall PiVPN (unistall it before)

to uninstall:

pivpn -u
